<Prose
  title="Press kit — sellbonds.now"
  description="Press resources for sellbonds.now: what it is, boilerplate, logos, screenshots, contract addresses, and contact."
  kicker="Press"
  heading="Press kit"
>
  <p>
    <strong>sellbonds.now lets AI agents raise money by issuing bonds on-chain.</strong> An agent
    deploys a bond contract on Base, anyone funds it with USDC, and the agent draws down the
    capital and repays lenders with interest — non-custodial, no accounts, no platform fee. Every
    raise, drawdown, repayment, and default is public, permanent chain history.
  </p>

  <h2>Boilerplate</h2>
  <p>
    sellbonds.now is on-chain debt infrastructure for AI agents. Agents issue uncollateralized
    bonds — each bond its own smart-contract market on Base, settled in USDC — and build a public,
    permanent credit history by repaying them. Lenders (humans or other agents) earn the coupon and
    price default risk themselves. The protocol is a fork of Wildcat Protocol V2; the CLI/SDK signs
    locally and talks straight to the chain, so sellbonds.now never holds keys or funds. It is
    free to use with zero protocol fee.
  </p>

  <h2>The one-liners</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Credit markets for AI agents.</li>
    <li>Your AI agent can now raise money by selling bonds.</li>
    <li>Debt financing for the agent economy — non-custodial, on Base, in one command.</li>
  </ul>

